WEBVTT

00:07.790 --> 00:09.705
You tried to kill Kevin.

00:09.835 --> 00:11.837
Help! Help!No! Shh!

00:11.968 --> 00:13.056
[Clank, woman shouts]

00:13.187 --> 00:14.362
Chuck's been cheating
on me.

00:14.492 --> 00:15.885
I'm offering you
something real.

00:16.016 --> 00:17.408
Being with you
is going to save me?

00:17.539 --> 00:18.670
It'd be an improvement.

00:18.801 --> 00:19.889
No, no, no.
Patti --

00:20.020 --> 00:21.456
I brought him
to the hospital.

00:21.586 --> 00:23.153
Having him sedated in there
is better

00:23.284 --> 00:24.633
than dead in my basement.

00:24.763 --> 00:26.113
At least now you're free
to focus

00:26.243 --> 00:27.679
on whatever you're doing
to Kevin.

00:27.810 --> 00:30.204
Somehow, I made him famous.
I can't kill him.

00:30.334 --> 00:32.597
I'm stuck here like this
until I die.

00:32.728 --> 00:33.946
I figured it out.

00:34.077 --> 00:35.339
I know what
we're going to do.

00:35.470 --> 00:36.732
[Computer beeps]Damn it!

00:38.516 --> 00:40.649
[Monitor beeping]Allison: Neil.

00:40.779 --> 00:43.739
[Indistinct announcement on PA]

00:43.869 --> 00:44.914
Neil.

00:47.264 --> 00:48.570
[Clatter]Hey.

00:48.700 --> 00:50.224
Jesus.

00:52.965 --> 00:55.403
Oh, the nightmare
continues.

00:55.533 --> 00:57.970
You're out of the basement.
It's an improvement, right?

00:58.101 --> 01:00.147
Like I'm supposed to
thank you?

01:00.277 --> 01:01.583
Patty got me here.

01:01.713 --> 01:03.237
Uh, no.

01:03.367 --> 01:05.717
No, both of us decided that
that had to happen.

01:05.848 --> 01:08.416
Please.
With what I have over you?

01:08.546 --> 01:10.940
Here's the thing, Neil --
you don't have anything over me.

01:11.071 --> 01:13.856
I own you.
What makes you think --

01:13.986 --> 01:16.467
We never tried
to kill Kevin.

01:16.598 --> 01:18.295
You did.

01:18.426 --> 01:22.125
You paid Nick to break in
and shoot Kevin in his sleep.

01:22.256 --> 01:23.953
Wait, you hired
that psycho?

01:24.084 --> 01:26.999
No. We have no
connection to him.

01:27.130 --> 01:29.089
Neither of us have
even met him before.

01:32.396 --> 01:34.659
I'm just
a helpless housewife.

01:34.790 --> 01:38.402
But you --
you have a record,

01:38.533 --> 01:41.710
and you knew Nick
from way back.

01:41.840 --> 01:44.582
You were on the hockey team
with him at Burncoat, right?

01:44.713 --> 01:47.150
Me and 15 other guys.

01:47.281 --> 01:49.109
Right, but none of them
were advertising

01:49.239 --> 01:50.893
the grudge
they had against Kevin

01:51.023 --> 01:54.549
to Detective Ridgeway
on the morning of the break-in.

01:54.679 --> 01:56.942
You came in yelling
to my apartment

01:57.073 --> 01:59.119
that Kevin
had betrayed you.

01:59.249 --> 02:01.686
So what?Patty: I know you know
what this means.

02:01.817 --> 02:05.821
All you have is a story,
and it sounds insane.

02:05.951 --> 02:08.476
And it doesn't really help
that it's coming from you.

02:08.606 --> 02:12.219
♪

02:12.349 --> 02:15.918
So, I guess when you
really think about it...

02:16.048 --> 02:18.268
who owns who?

02:18.399 --> 02:20.444
Patty: Do you really think
that's gonna keep him quiet?

02:20.575 --> 02:21.663
I don't know.

02:21.793 --> 02:22.925
[Sighs]

02:23.055 --> 02:26.668
[Indistinct announcement on PA]

02:26.798 --> 02:28.278
Your neck looks better.

02:28.409 --> 02:30.585
Yeah, 'cause I have like a pound
of concealer on it.

02:30.715 --> 02:32.804
I think maybe just keeping this
all hidden right now

02:32.935 --> 02:33.979
is the right thing to do.

02:34.110 --> 02:36.025
What about after that?

02:36.156 --> 02:40.029
It's not exactly true that we
don't have a connection to Nick.

02:40.160 --> 02:43.250
I have
a longer-term solution.

02:43.380 --> 02:44.947
Ah, is that what your voicemail
was about?

02:45.077 --> 02:46.427
It sounded like a riddle.

02:46.557 --> 02:48.690
"I'm fine. Put it all on me.
I figured it out."

02:48.820 --> 02:51.083
Sorry, I think I was still
a little drunk when I left that,

02:51.214 --> 02:52.389
but, um...

02:52.520 --> 02:53.956
there's a Dunkin
across the street.

02:54.086 --> 02:56.611
Let's go have some donuts
and I'll fill you in, okay?

02:56.741 --> 02:58.090
No.

02:58.221 --> 03:00.180
Okay, not somedonuts.
Adonut.

03:00.310 --> 03:03.052
No. I mean...

03:03.183 --> 03:04.706
[Whispering] I don't want
to know what you're doing.

03:07.448 --> 03:10.233
I really don't want
to know anything anymore.

03:10.364 --> 03:11.756
I'm trying to fix this.

03:11.887 --> 03:13.889
And how does that
usually go, Allison?

03:18.023 --> 03:22.550
Look, this has been
the worst 72 hours of my life,

03:22.680 --> 03:24.682
and I meant it
when I said I'm out.

03:27.381 --> 03:28.512
Okay.

03:28.643 --> 03:31.036
So, I'm gonna go home,
I'm gonna get in bed

03:31.167 --> 03:34.214
until they discharge him
in the morning.

03:34.344 --> 03:38.000
-Fine.
-Please do the same.

03:39.480 --> 03:47.357
♪

03:47.488 --> 03:55.496
♪

03:57.106 --> 03:57.933
[Laughter]

03:58.063 --> 04:00.196
[Teakettle whistling]

04:10.902 --> 04:12.252
Allison: Oh.

04:15.516 --> 04:17.387
[Sobbing]

04:20.521 --> 04:23.611
Tanya Iacono.

04:23.741 --> 04:25.047
You remember Tanya?

04:25.177 --> 04:26.614
'Course.
Lost her virginity

04:26.744 --> 04:29.443
to Jay McMahon in the bathroom
at Chuck E. Cheese

04:29.573 --> 04:30.792
in Fitchburg.

04:30.922 --> 04:33.621
[Sobs]

04:33.751 --> 04:35.492
Awful.

04:35.623 --> 04:37.712
I feel for you.

04:37.842 --> 04:39.279
I do.

04:39.409 --> 04:41.803
But I'm usually the one
catching the affair.

04:41.933 --> 04:43.892
So, what are you
looking for from me?

04:45.459 --> 04:47.852
Well, this -- this
was my niece's idea.

04:47.983 --> 04:49.637
We wanted to see
what kind of services

04:49.767 --> 04:52.292
you offer
to someone like Diane.

04:52.422 --> 04:54.555
Someone who doesn't
realistically

04:54.685 --> 04:56.252
have the option
of divorce.

04:56.383 --> 04:58.341
I-I don't?

04:58.472 --> 05:00.822
It's expensive.
It would take years.

05:00.952 --> 05:03.215
It would take Chuck
actually letting you leave.

05:03.346 --> 05:07.089
So, um, do you
just look into people,

05:07.219 --> 05:10.658
or can you kind of
order off the menu?

05:10.788 --> 05:12.137
So you're looking
for a way out?

05:12.268 --> 05:14.749
Well, I --Yes. Yes.

05:14.879 --> 05:17.752
Um, I have heard of women,
you know, getting out.

05:17.882 --> 05:19.231
They just disappear.

05:19.362 --> 05:22.060
People assume that they --
that they died.

05:22.191 --> 05:24.193
So, how realistic
is that?

05:24.324 --> 05:26.282
You ever see "Snapped"?

05:26.413 --> 05:27.762
No.

05:27.892 --> 05:29.938
Do I look like someone
who would watch that?

05:30.068 --> 05:32.549
I'm just saying,
doing it is realistic.

05:32.680 --> 05:34.464
Diane getting away
with it's another thing.

05:34.595 --> 05:37.119
I'm sorry. I-I'm not even sure
I want to leave Chuck,

05:37.249 --> 05:38.599
and now I'm
on "Snapped"?

05:38.729 --> 05:40.296
No, no, no, no, no.
But, um --

05:40.427 --> 05:42.080
[Cellphone ringing]Oh.

05:42.211 --> 05:44.039
Ugh.
He's calling.

05:44.169 --> 05:47.085
Ah.Do -- Do you believe?

05:47.216 --> 05:49.349
Yes?

05:49.479 --> 05:52.221
Oh, you have got
to be kidding me.

05:52.352 --> 05:53.962
[Laughs]

05:54.092 --> 05:55.572
Yeah.
Well, it's not my fault

05:55.703 --> 05:57.748
you don't know where
the can opener is, okay?

05:57.879 --> 05:59.359
I don't use it.

05:59.489 --> 06:01.143
No, I did not hide it.

06:01.273 --> 06:05.103
It is a can opener,
not a Fabra-Jay Egg.

06:05.234 --> 06:07.584
Excuse me
for just a moment.'Course.

06:07.715 --> 06:10.500
None of your business
who I'm talking to.

06:10.631 --> 06:13.155
Diane: Oh, well, that's
something coming from you!

06:13.285 --> 06:15.462
Someone who got more hair
on your back

06:15.592 --> 06:17.768
than you've ever
had on your face!

06:17.899 --> 06:19.770
Marriage, right?

06:19.901 --> 06:23.208
Oh, yeah! Oh, no!
Tell me another one!

06:23.339 --> 06:26.908
So --It was real nice of you
to bring your aunt down here.

06:27.038 --> 06:29.127
Out of the kindness
of your heart.

06:29.258 --> 06:31.652
Yeah, well, she's family.

06:31.782 --> 06:36.091
Yeah. She paid the $350 retainer
to talk to me.

06:36.221 --> 06:37.440
Moron!

06:37.571 --> 06:39.964
Do you have $350?Moron! Yes.

06:40.095 --> 06:43.315
Now you understand it?

06:43.446 --> 06:46.580
I told you...

06:46.710 --> 06:48.320
Feel free to come back
when you do.

06:48.451 --> 06:50.105
Move over!

06:50.235 --> 06:52.934
Well, it's not my fault that
we don't have better Wi-Fi!

06:55.458 --> 06:58.069
[Keys clatter]

06:58.200 --> 07:00.507
[Groans]

07:00.637 --> 07:02.117
[Knock on door]

07:02.247 --> 07:03.597
♪

07:03.727 --> 07:06.034
[Knocking continues]

07:06.164 --> 07:07.601
[Whimpers]

07:07.731 --> 07:12.780
♪

07:12.910 --> 07:14.346
Hi.

07:14.477 --> 07:16.261
Hi.
I know.

07:16.392 --> 07:17.480
People who show up
at front doors

07:17.611 --> 07:19.264
without calling
are very intense,

07:19.395 --> 07:20.701
but the electricity
is out at my place,

07:20.831 --> 07:22.659
which means my phone is dead
and my heat is off,

07:22.790 --> 07:24.400
and I swear, if I spend
one more minute there,

07:24.531 --> 07:26.446
I might lose my little toe
to frostbite.

07:26.576 --> 07:28.970
Oh.And it's the cute toe.

07:29.100 --> 07:31.146
The other ones kind of
just look like peanut shells.

07:31.276 --> 07:33.583
Gosh, they're all cute.

07:33.714 --> 07:35.063
So you want
to stay here?

07:35.193 --> 07:37.674
Just until the power company
gets its act together.

07:37.805 --> 07:40.285
Unless it's a bad time?

07:40.416 --> 07:43.332
Not at all.
Come in.

07:43.463 --> 07:44.507
Mwah.

07:44.638 --> 07:48.642
♪

07:48.772 --> 07:49.643
[Door closes]

07:49.773 --> 07:51.427
♪

07:51.558 --> 07:54.952
Hey, um, I'm glad
we did this today.

07:55.083 --> 07:57.520
The PI and the coffee.

07:57.651 --> 07:59.522
I've missed you.
Ah.

07:59.653 --> 08:01.263
Yeah, you too, sweets.

08:01.393 --> 08:03.352
God, you know, you ask for light
with cream and sugar,

08:03.483 --> 08:04.832
and they always skimp.

08:13.318 --> 08:15.712
You know, I was thinking
I'd get to see you even more

08:15.843 --> 08:19.499
if, uh, I started working
at the liquor store again.

08:19.629 --> 08:23.285
I thought you got that cushy
waitressing job at the diner.

08:23.415 --> 08:25.417
Well, I do, but it's only
part time, and I'm --

08:25.548 --> 08:27.158
I'm just trying
to save up right now.

08:27.289 --> 08:28.899
Oh, yeah?
For what?

08:29.030 --> 08:30.727
Vacation.

08:30.858 --> 08:32.773
Mm.

08:32.903 --> 08:35.645
Well, I already hired
Frankie DeLanzo's kid.

08:35.776 --> 08:38.343
You know, he smells like one of
those teen stores at the mall,

08:38.474 --> 08:41.608
but, uh, he does not quit on me
in the middle of a workday.

08:41.738 --> 08:43.610
Ah.
If you need cash quick,
you know,

08:43.740 --> 08:45.307
why don't you
just hock something?

08:45.437 --> 08:47.439
Like at a pawnshop?Yes.

08:47.570 --> 08:50.442
It's a perfectly
respectable thing to do.

08:50.573 --> 08:52.183
Compared to what?

08:52.314 --> 08:56.274
Oh, look, I needed money for
girls' weekend at Foxwoods,

08:56.405 --> 08:58.973
and Chuck said no,
so what did I do?

08:59.103 --> 09:01.323
I, uh, pawned
his gold chain.

09:01.453 --> 09:03.194
He hadn't worn it
in 10 years.

09:03.325 --> 09:05.109
Didn't even notice.

09:05.240 --> 09:07.547
Maybe we can find
something else of Chuck's.

09:07.677 --> 09:10.767
Well, Chuck thinks
a can opener's valuable, so...

09:10.898 --> 09:12.943
Does Kevin
have a gold chain?

09:13.074 --> 09:16.077
No, Kevin says man jewelry
is for "I-talians."

09:16.207 --> 09:18.645
[Laughs]

09:18.775 --> 09:22.823
Oh. You know, maybe there's
something in the storage unit.

09:22.953 --> 09:25.347
What storage unit?Oh, it's Chuck's.

09:25.477 --> 09:27.175
Kevin put a bunch
of his valuables in there

09:27.305 --> 09:28.611
after the break-in.

09:28.742 --> 09:32.441
♪

09:32.572 --> 09:35.662
Any way you can
get me in there?

09:35.792 --> 09:40.492
Uh, I mean, I'd have to
steal Chuck's key.

09:40.623 --> 09:42.451
So, sure. Yeah.

09:42.582 --> 09:44.932
♪

09:48.500 --> 09:55.551
♪

09:55.682 --> 10:02.819
♪

10:02.950 --> 10:05.126
Tammy: You don't have to
clean for me.

10:05.256 --> 10:07.171
What?
But you're a guest,

10:07.302 --> 10:09.043
and guests are blessed
and deserve your best.

10:09.173 --> 10:11.045
[Chuckles]

10:11.175 --> 10:12.568
Allison says that.

10:12.699 --> 10:21.359
♪

10:21.490 --> 10:30.194
♪

10:30.325 --> 10:32.414
I'm donating it.

10:32.544 --> 10:33.763
And others.

10:33.894 --> 10:36.244
You've been reading
that one for a while.

10:36.374 --> 10:38.072
I need a Red Bull.

10:38.202 --> 10:39.813
You want anything?

10:42.250 --> 10:43.773
Is that Neil?

10:43.904 --> 10:46.950
♪

10:47.081 --> 10:49.910
[Door opens, closes]

10:50.040 --> 10:53.043
♪

10:53.174 --> 10:54.697
Hey.

10:54.828 --> 10:56.873
♪

10:57.004 --> 10:58.092
Hi.

10:58.222 --> 11:00.529
♪

11:00.660 --> 11:02.052
What are you
doing out here?

11:02.183 --> 11:04.576
They discharged me early.

11:04.707 --> 11:08.102
Okay, um, it's --

11:08.232 --> 11:11.105
it's freezing out,
so go inside,

11:11.235 --> 11:12.759
'cause you look --

11:12.889 --> 11:16.240
♪

11:16.371 --> 11:18.590
Well,
you've looked better.

11:18.721 --> 11:21.115
Really? 'Cause, you know,
I feel terrific

11:21.245 --> 11:22.856
after getting bottled and
bleeding from the head for --[Door opens, closes]

11:22.986 --> 11:24.335
Tammy: Hey.

11:24.466 --> 11:25.989
How's it going, Neil?

11:26.120 --> 11:27.817
I was just telling Patty,
it's been a rough couple days,

11:27.948 --> 11:31.255
but really nice
of you two to check in.

11:31.386 --> 11:33.301
And Allison.

11:33.431 --> 11:35.129
Hi.
Hi.

11:35.259 --> 11:37.566
Hi.Hi.

11:37.697 --> 11:39.046
Hi.

11:39.176 --> 11:42.658
♪

11:42.789 --> 11:44.051
This is fun.

11:44.181 --> 11:46.009
♪

11:46.140 --> 11:48.664
So, what do you think
of my new haircut?

11:48.795 --> 11:51.101
I love it.

11:51.232 --> 11:53.016
Sometimes
a transformational haircut

11:53.147 --> 11:54.496
can be a good thing,
right?

11:54.626 --> 11:57.586
Sometimes.

11:57.717 --> 12:00.023
Yeah, well,
wasn't really my choice.

12:00.154 --> 12:04.941
Doctors shaved a weird patch
to staple a giant wound.

12:05.072 --> 12:05.942
Oh!

12:06.073 --> 12:08.771
I'm so sorry.
I, uh --

12:08.902 --> 12:11.426
That --
It looks so painful.

12:11.556 --> 12:13.558
I'm just --
I'm sorry that happened.

12:13.689 --> 12:15.430
Yeah,
that is pretty gross.

12:15.560 --> 12:17.737
Tammy, can you believe
I got such bad food poisoning,

12:17.867 --> 12:21.131
I passed out and hit my head on
the tile floor of the bathroom?

12:21.262 --> 12:23.177
Yes.
He had that, uh --

12:23.307 --> 12:25.483
He had that thing
that I had.

12:25.614 --> 12:27.007
The bug.

12:27.137 --> 12:28.486
A few days ago.

12:28.617 --> 12:30.445
Yeah, that bug.

12:30.575 --> 12:31.838
Yeah, that bug.

12:31.968 --> 12:35.102
♪

12:35.232 --> 12:38.061
Okay, well,
if you need anything,

12:38.192 --> 12:39.236
we're right downstairs.

12:39.367 --> 12:43.153
Yes.
I will just...

12:43.284 --> 12:45.286
-Oh. Sorry.
-Sorry.

12:45.416 --> 12:46.722
-Bye.
-Bye.

12:46.853 --> 12:48.332
-Okay.
-Bye, there. Bye.

12:48.463 --> 12:49.464
Mm-hmm.

12:52.380 --> 12:54.034
[Door opens]

13:02.912 --> 13:04.653
[Screaming][Glass shatters]

13:05.567 --> 13:07.134
[Groans]

13:07.264 --> 13:14.837
♪

13:14.968 --> 13:22.497
♪

13:22.627 --> 13:30.244
♪

13:30.374 --> 13:32.899
Allison, you home?

13:33.029 --> 13:34.378
Oh, Neil?

13:34.509 --> 13:36.380
Kev!
Oh, buddy!

13:36.511 --> 13:37.817
[Laughs]

13:37.947 --> 13:40.950
Oh, I'm sorry I was gone
for so long.

13:41.081 --> 13:43.561
I appreciate that, but maybe
you should apologize

13:43.692 --> 13:46.173
for this hair first.
Oh, my gosh.

13:46.303 --> 13:48.218
I mean, I know this is never
what somebody wants to hear

13:48.349 --> 13:51.787
right after a haircut,
but what happened?

13:51.918 --> 13:53.571
I actually --I mean, 'cause you have

13:53.702 --> 13:57.053
the general vibe
of a sad dog in a cone.

13:57.184 --> 13:58.838
That's true.
A lot went down --

13:58.968 --> 14:01.405
Like, you know how they say
that sore thumbs stick out?

14:01.536 --> 14:03.146
You actually
look like that.

14:03.277 --> 14:07.716
Like -- Like a big, red,
angry, sore thumb.

14:07.847 --> 14:10.414
What the hell
happened, man?

14:10.545 --> 14:13.156
I, um --

14:13.287 --> 14:16.681
I passed out when I got food
poisoning and cracked my head.

14:16.812 --> 14:18.031
I-I had to get stitches.

14:18.161 --> 14:19.293
It hurts so --I was gonna guess

14:19.423 --> 14:20.947
that you got gum
stuck in there

14:21.077 --> 14:22.687
when you passed out
in a gutter.

14:22.818 --> 14:24.776
Oh, God!
I was close!

14:24.907 --> 14:26.256
But I'm -- I'm fine.

14:26.387 --> 14:30.304
I'm back, and I will always
be here for you.

14:30.434 --> 14:35.657
Well, that is excellent,
if not a little intense.

14:35.787 --> 14:39.748
But it's actually, uh,
got me thinking.

14:39.879 --> 14:41.837
You know,
as a newly minted

14:41.968 --> 14:45.101
and very, very busy
local celebrity,

14:45.232 --> 14:48.713
I'm --
I'm quite overwhelmed.

14:48.844 --> 14:50.106
I-I get it, man.
I mean, I feel like --

14:50.237 --> 14:52.587
You know, I have this
big interview coming up,

14:52.717 --> 14:54.676
I've got
ribbon-cutting ceremonies,

14:54.806 --> 14:58.854
and, of course, I still have
my regular 9:00-to-3:00 job.

14:58.985 --> 15:02.292
And I'm big enough to admit
when I need help.

15:02.423 --> 15:03.946
Help sounds great.
Yeah, thank you.

15:04.077 --> 15:05.600
Which is exactly
what I wanted to hear,

15:05.730 --> 15:09.691
because I have the opportunity
of a lifetime for you.

15:09.821 --> 15:12.520
I choose you
to be my altar boy.

15:12.650 --> 15:14.348
My go-to guy.

15:14.478 --> 15:16.654
My Girl Friday!

15:16.785 --> 15:19.092
Except I'm a boy.

15:19.222 --> 15:22.399
Except you're a boy.
[Laughs]

15:22.530 --> 15:25.750
You are gonna be
my new official assistant.

15:25.881 --> 15:28.928
Oh. A distraction
does sound pretty good.

15:29.058 --> 15:31.582
Great!
But the job is devotion, Neil.

15:31.713 --> 15:33.367
You'll put
your own problems aside

15:33.497 --> 15:36.370
and think
of only me, 24/7.

15:36.500 --> 15:37.849
That sounds...

15:37.980 --> 15:39.677
amazing.

15:39.808 --> 15:41.766
Ah! Oop!

15:42.724 --> 15:44.508
Both: I'll have
what she's having!

15:44.639 --> 15:45.727
Blblblbl!

15:45.857 --> 15:48.034
[Both laugh]

15:48.164 --> 15:49.731
Alright, well,
enough with this nonsense.

15:49.861 --> 15:52.081
You're on the clock.
Get me some pizza rolls.Okay.

15:52.212 --> 15:55.824
♪

15:58.087 --> 16:00.350
Welcome to Chuck's
super-crucial storage unit.

16:00.481 --> 16:02.700
40 bucks a month because
he wouldn't throw away

16:02.831 --> 16:04.354
an airplane propeller
coffee table.

16:04.485 --> 16:05.747
Uh-huh.

16:05.877 --> 16:08.576
Kevin's stuff's over there.
[Sighs]

16:10.143 --> 16:12.232
You okay, D?
Oh, yeah.

16:12.362 --> 16:16.323
I always burst a blood vessel
if I cry too hard.

16:16.453 --> 16:18.455
So what are we
looking for again?

16:18.586 --> 16:22.677
We are looking
for a stupid goddamn...

16:22.807 --> 16:24.505
Wade Boggs rookie card.

16:24.635 --> 16:28.074
I wonder how much of our rent
he spent on this.

16:28.204 --> 16:30.163
You got these?

16:30.293 --> 16:33.644
Ah. Yeah.
Grandma left them to me.

16:33.775 --> 16:35.733
I used to wear them all the time
until I met Kevin

16:35.864 --> 16:37.605
and he said
they made me look like

16:37.735 --> 16:39.999
a poor man's
Wilma Flintstone.

16:40.129 --> 16:42.044
Those are
the same ones, huh?

16:42.175 --> 16:44.046
Yeah, I always figured
they were fake.

16:44.177 --> 16:47.354
You used to wear them to work
at the Packie under your smock.

16:47.484 --> 16:48.442
Yeah.

16:48.572 --> 16:50.096
♪

16:50.226 --> 16:51.445
I like them.

16:51.575 --> 16:54.056
Eh. I do see the
Wilma Flintstone thing.

16:54.187 --> 16:55.884
Kevin's still gonna
say something.

16:56.015 --> 16:57.538
♪

16:57.668 --> 16:59.583
[Vehicle approaches]

16:59.714 --> 17:00.976
You know what?

17:01.107 --> 17:02.630
I don't care.

17:02.760 --> 17:04.545
[Vehicle door opens]

17:04.675 --> 17:06.329
♪

17:06.460 --> 17:08.027
Oh, my God.
It's Neil.

17:08.157 --> 17:10.899
Um, shoot!
Shoot!

17:11.030 --> 17:14.250
♪

17:14.381 --> 17:15.643
Hey.

17:15.773 --> 17:17.253
'Sup?

17:17.384 --> 17:19.516
I'm just here to grab
Kevin's lucky Red Sox hat

17:19.647 --> 17:22.041
before I pick up
his hot sauce samples.

17:22.171 --> 17:24.304
I'm Kevin's
assistant now.

17:24.434 --> 17:26.958
Yeah, uh,
that's, uh --

17:27.089 --> 17:29.309
I was just here
to pick up...

17:29.439 --> 17:31.833
my can opener.

17:31.963 --> 17:32.877
Ha!

17:33.008 --> 17:35.228
My can opener.

17:35.358 --> 17:37.056
You wanna see?

17:37.186 --> 17:39.145
Sure. Oops.

17:39.275 --> 17:40.450
Neil: Dropped it.

17:40.581 --> 17:42.235
Oh, shiny.

17:42.365 --> 17:45.455
♪

17:45.586 --> 17:47.979
It's nice.

17:48.110 --> 17:50.199
Yeah.
Well, you know, just --

17:50.330 --> 17:52.419
Yeah.
I'm gonna...

17:52.549 --> 17:55.378
Okay. Yeah, it's in one
of these boxes somewhere.

17:55.509 --> 17:57.380
I'm gonna open a can.

17:57.511 --> 17:58.599
Okay.

17:58.729 --> 17:59.817
♪

17:59.948 --> 18:01.210
Bye.

18:01.341 --> 18:02.559
♪

18:02.690 --> 18:04.257
Diane, who knew?

18:04.387 --> 18:06.302
Ow. Stupid --

18:06.433 --> 18:07.956
Alright, where are you?

18:08.087 --> 18:14.789
♪

18:14.919 --> 18:21.665
♪

18:21.796 --> 18:24.538
Chinese.

18:24.668 --> 18:25.800
Fun.

18:25.930 --> 18:27.715
♪

18:27.845 --> 18:30.109
Are you okay?

18:30.239 --> 18:32.241
Yeah. Yeah.

18:32.372 --> 18:33.721
Fine.

18:33.851 --> 18:34.852
I'm great.

18:34.983 --> 18:38.073
♪

18:38.204 --> 18:41.859
So, work's been a lot.

18:41.990 --> 18:44.601
That guy who broke
into Allison's?

18:44.732 --> 18:46.734
He had some weird pill bottle
on him when he did.

18:46.864 --> 18:50.129
The only one
not from Fiore's.

18:50.259 --> 18:51.782
That's weird.

18:51.913 --> 18:54.002
It's just one of those things
that you'll never understand

18:54.133 --> 18:55.699
and you have to let go.

18:55.830 --> 18:57.875
Every case has them.

18:58.006 --> 18:59.573
But this guy...

18:59.703 --> 19:01.096
I don't know.

19:01.227 --> 19:02.489
He was weird?

19:02.619 --> 19:04.099
Yes, it feels
like an itch.

19:04.230 --> 19:11.150
♪

19:11.280 --> 19:13.935
Mm.
Not that one.

19:14.065 --> 19:16.416
Has cashews.
So?

19:16.546 --> 19:18.157
So you hate cashews.

19:18.287 --> 19:19.332
Yeah, but how
do you know that?

19:19.462 --> 19:21.029
Because I pay attention.

19:21.160 --> 19:29.168
♪

19:29.298 --> 19:30.256
I thought
you wanted to quit.

19:30.386 --> 19:31.779
I changed my mind.

19:31.909 --> 19:37.219
♪

19:37.350 --> 19:39.526
[Dog barking in distance]

19:43.182 --> 19:45.184
-Hey.
-Hey.

19:59.676 --> 20:03.027
♪

20:04.812 --> 20:06.509
Nope, nope, nope!
You're banned from the kitchen.

20:06.640 --> 20:08.511
Pip-pip,
get out of here.

20:08.642 --> 20:11.558
Can I be pip-pip banned
from the whole house?

20:11.688 --> 20:13.560
It's just the next two hours,
okay?

20:13.690 --> 20:16.432
I need space. I'm prepping
for my big newspaper interview.

20:16.563 --> 20:18.347
You're drinking while wearing
tiny glasses.

20:18.478 --> 20:21.002
That's not prepping.

20:21.132 --> 20:23.134
Ah.
I should have known.

20:23.265 --> 20:25.876
You always act
all high and mighty

20:26.007 --> 20:28.009
when you wear
those pearls.

20:28.139 --> 20:30.620
What, you think
you're better than me?

20:30.751 --> 20:32.100
Yes.

20:32.231 --> 20:33.928
Well, do you have
a huge interview

20:34.058 --> 20:35.582
with the Worcester paper?

20:35.712 --> 20:38.541
No. And it's gonna decide
whether the Worcester Wild Dude

20:38.672 --> 20:41.762
is a flash in the pan
or a household brand.

20:41.892 --> 20:45.635
Like Coca-Cola
but for Wild Dudes.

20:45.766 --> 20:48.203
I think
that's Mountain Dew.

20:48.334 --> 20:49.465
Oh, wait, wait.
Uh --

20:49.596 --> 20:51.119
Oh, just let me
be banned.

20:51.250 --> 20:53.643
Uh, my dad says that
the Wild Dude

20:53.774 --> 20:56.255
is more aspirational
if he's not married,

20:56.385 --> 20:59.954
so if you see the interviewer,
we're cousins, cool?

21:01.216 --> 21:02.957
Well, being related to you
is less pathetic

21:03.087 --> 21:04.959
than being married
to you, so...

21:05.089 --> 21:10.007
♪

21:10.138 --> 21:12.009
[Indistinct conversations]

21:12.140 --> 21:19.974
♪

21:20.104 --> 21:21.192
Hello.

21:21.323 --> 21:24.848
♪

21:24.979 --> 21:26.633
Allison.

21:26.763 --> 21:29.679
Okay,
so you're still upset.

21:29.810 --> 21:32.856
What do you mean?You only call me Allison
when you're pissed off at me.

21:32.987 --> 21:34.423
That's not true.

21:34.554 --> 21:35.903
Yes, it is.

21:36.033 --> 21:37.687
You also like to play
with things on the counter

21:37.818 --> 21:39.472
when you're
feeling flirty.

21:39.602 --> 21:41.082
You're like...

21:41.212 --> 21:43.171
Shoot.
Jesus, Allison.

21:43.302 --> 21:45.042
Shoot!

21:45.173 --> 21:46.435
See? [Chuckles]

21:46.566 --> 21:48.437
♪

21:48.568 --> 21:51.832
I know that we both, uh, said
some things the other day --

21:51.962 --> 21:53.399
Said?

21:53.529 --> 21:55.009
Yelled. We yelled some things
the other day.

21:55.139 --> 21:56.358
Mm-hmm.

21:56.489 --> 21:59.230
But we've known
each other so long.

21:59.361 --> 22:01.407
Can we just try?

22:01.537 --> 22:03.670
♪

22:03.800 --> 22:05.933
Yeah. Sure.

22:06.063 --> 22:09.110
Good. Great.

22:09.240 --> 22:12.418
So, Sam, how are you?

22:12.548 --> 22:13.984
♪

22:14.115 --> 22:15.029
I'm good.
How are you?

22:15.159 --> 22:16.291
Mm.

22:16.422 --> 22:17.510
I'm good.

22:17.640 --> 22:21.165
♪

22:21.296 --> 22:24.299
Well, in the same of our deep
and longstanding friendship,

22:24.430 --> 22:28.564
um, I'm in a bit of a
tough position right now,

22:28.695 --> 22:31.001
and I need some money,
so I was hoping that --

22:31.132 --> 22:32.133
Okay,
I'm gonna stop you.

22:32.263 --> 22:35.397
Um, I'm sorry you're
going through

22:35.528 --> 22:37.747
whatever you're
going through today,

22:37.878 --> 22:41.229
but, uh...

22:41.360 --> 22:43.623
I can't give you
your job back.

22:43.753 --> 22:45.189
W-What?

22:45.320 --> 22:47.844
No, I-I was just --
I was gonna ask you

22:47.975 --> 22:50.369
if your uncle still owns
that pawnshop in Sudbury.

22:50.499 --> 22:52.588
But I-I don't
work here anymore?

22:52.719 --> 22:54.808
You didn't want my help
anymore, right?Well, I never said that.

22:54.938 --> 22:56.897
Oh, yeah, that's right.
Yeah, you yelledit.

22:57.027 --> 23:01.467
Look, I-I know I-I've been
a lot lately, okay?[Chuckling] Okay.

23:01.597 --> 23:04.644
But I really am
trying, okay?

23:04.774 --> 23:06.559
All I want
is to be Allie again.

23:06.689 --> 23:10.693
♪

23:10.824 --> 23:13.261
I understand.

23:13.392 --> 23:17.265
But I can't work
with you anymore.

23:17.396 --> 23:19.528
Fine.

23:19.659 --> 23:21.269
And my uncle who owned
the pawnshop died.

23:21.400 --> 23:22.923
Great.

23:23.053 --> 23:26.883
No. I -- I'm so sorry
that he di--

23:27.014 --> 23:29.190
that he has passed on.

23:29.320 --> 23:30.844
He was very nice.

23:30.974 --> 23:34.369
♪

23:34.500 --> 23:35.675
[Door opens]

23:35.805 --> 23:37.546
[Door creaks]

23:39.896 --> 23:41.898
Neil?

23:42.029 --> 23:44.553
Neil!

23:44.684 --> 23:45.989
What are you doing?

23:46.120 --> 23:48.035
I need a hat.You're wearing a hat.

23:48.165 --> 23:50.951
I know I'm wearing a hat,
but I need a different one.

23:51.081 --> 23:53.519
I promised Kevin I'd find
his vintage Red Sox hat,

23:53.649 --> 23:55.738
but I went to the storage unit
and dug through everything,

23:55.869 --> 23:57.740
and it still
wasn't there!

23:57.871 --> 24:00.177
Ah, shit!

24:00.308 --> 24:02.092
Shut up.

24:02.223 --> 24:04.268
Tammy is right downstairs.

24:04.399 --> 24:06.401
[Breathing heavily]

24:10.710 --> 24:13.190
Neil? Neil.

24:13.321 --> 24:14.931
Please.

24:15.062 --> 24:17.499
Please don't say or do
anything stupid, okay?

24:17.630 --> 24:19.414
If you start this thing
with Allison,

24:19.545 --> 24:21.068
it's just gonna
cause you more trouble.

24:21.198 --> 24:22.809
And you're already --

24:27.944 --> 24:29.816
If you need help
or something...

24:32.427 --> 24:33.776
...I'm around.

24:36.518 --> 24:40.827
♪

24:40.957 --> 24:42.176
Get out.

24:42.306 --> 24:44.918
♪

24:45.048 --> 24:47.181
I said get out.

24:47.311 --> 24:53.448
♪

24:53.579 --> 24:59.672
♪

24:59.802 --> 25:01.935
[Door opens]

25:02.065 --> 25:03.502
[Door closes]

25:03.632 --> 25:06.156
[Siren wailing in distance]

25:14.251 --> 25:17.037
You got to wait
till this one closes.

25:17.167 --> 25:18.342
Ah.

25:18.473 --> 25:22.346
[Rock music playing]

25:22.477 --> 25:25.045
-What's in there?
-Smirnoff.

25:25.175 --> 25:27.438
-And?
-Ice.

25:27.569 --> 25:28.614
You want my help here
or not?

25:28.744 --> 25:30.224
Yeah. Sorry.
Yes.

25:30.354 --> 25:32.356
♪

25:32.487 --> 25:33.444
Hello.

25:33.575 --> 25:36.360
♪

25:36.491 --> 25:40.626
Hello. Uh, we would like
to pawn an item.

25:40.756 --> 25:43.019
Yep.
No shit.

25:43.150 --> 25:44.368
Hey, James.

25:45.500 --> 25:48.024
Diane. Hey.

25:48.155 --> 25:50.636
Um, sorry to hear
about Chuck and Tanya.

25:50.766 --> 25:55.292
Yeah, so we're looking
to get about $400.

25:55.423 --> 25:58.252
That's Wade Boggs.
Rookie card.

25:58.382 --> 25:59.819
It's worth
at least that.

25:59.949 --> 26:03.736
♪

26:03.866 --> 26:05.607
I could do $275.

26:05.738 --> 26:08.392
Okay,
she's my niece, okay?

26:08.523 --> 26:11.744
You can't screw her over.
So come on, $375.

26:11.874 --> 26:13.963
♪

26:14.094 --> 26:17.010
Fine, but don't tell anyone
I go easy on you.

26:17.140 --> 26:19.273
♪

26:19.403 --> 26:21.231
All this
for a vacation, huh?

26:21.362 --> 26:25.105
You really think a weekend in
Branson is gonna fix everything?

26:25.235 --> 26:27.324
Worcester's a trap,
Diane.

26:27.455 --> 26:30.501
Well, that's a nice thing to say
to someone who still lives here.

26:30.632 --> 26:31.938
So do I.

26:32.068 --> 26:33.417
Doesn't mean
we can't leave.

26:33.548 --> 26:35.115
[Keyboard clacking]

26:35.245 --> 26:37.987
♪

26:38.118 --> 26:41.338
Yeah, um, I can't give you
anything for this.

26:41.469 --> 26:42.775
I'm actually gonna
have to take it.

26:42.905 --> 26:45.691
Take it and not give me
any money?

26:45.821 --> 26:48.345
That's not how --
not how pawn works.

26:48.476 --> 26:52.262
Yes, thank you,
but this is stolen.

26:52.393 --> 26:55.135
Oh, no. It --
No. It's not.

26:55.265 --> 26:57.833
Um, it's my husband's.

26:57.964 --> 26:59.618
So, legally, it is mine.

26:59.748 --> 27:01.141
Property-wise.
'Kay?

27:01.271 --> 27:02.751
It's not --
It is not stolen.

27:02.882 --> 27:05.493
Maybe you didn't do it,
but this was stolen.

27:05.624 --> 27:08.452
It's in a database here
as belonging to Brenda Daly.

27:08.583 --> 27:10.759
Stolen eight years ago.

27:10.890 --> 27:13.414
See the back right here?
"To Brenda."

27:13.544 --> 27:15.721
♪

27:15.851 --> 27:19.202
I'm gonna have to report this
to the police.

27:19.333 --> 27:20.551
Oh. N--

27:20.682 --> 27:27.515
♪

27:27.646 --> 27:30.692
[Laughs]
You are not.

27:30.823 --> 27:32.738
[Both laughing]

27:34.391 --> 27:36.176
[Laughs nervously]

27:36.306 --> 27:37.743
Who do you think I am?

27:37.873 --> 27:39.745
That do-gooder Timmy Cray
over at Pawn-Porium?

27:39.875 --> 27:42.486
[Laughter]

27:42.617 --> 27:45.185
But, um, I am gonna
have to take this.

27:46.752 --> 27:48.841
God damn it, Kevin.

27:53.584 --> 27:55.674
♪

27:55.804 --> 27:58.720
You know, I've actually been
in the newspaper before.

27:58.851 --> 28:02.289
Once upon a time,
I was Worcester's largest baby,

28:02.419 --> 28:04.770
14 pounds, 12 ounces.

28:04.900 --> 28:07.773
Natural delivery,
of course.

28:07.903 --> 28:09.252
Wow. That's...

28:09.383 --> 28:11.124
Wow.
Yep.

28:11.254 --> 28:13.387
My head stayed pretty much
the same size

28:13.517 --> 28:15.868
since the day
I was born.

28:15.998 --> 28:17.347
Tip of the hat
to your mother.

28:17.478 --> 28:19.001
She's dead.

28:19.132 --> 28:21.700
Uh, feel free to include
all of this in the article.

28:21.830 --> 28:24.790
Ah, yes, my, uh,
assistant is back.

28:26.792 --> 28:31.405
Hi. I'm Kevin's assistant
and fun partner, Neil.

28:31.535 --> 28:34.321
Bad news.
I couldn't get the hat.

28:34.451 --> 28:36.323
Did you even look for it?Well, of course I did, but --

28:36.453 --> 28:39.195
"Buts" are for excuses
and strip clubs, Neil.

28:39.326 --> 28:42.459
Did you at least bring
my buffalo sauce samples?

28:42.590 --> 28:46.681
I sure did.
No "if"s, "and"s, or "asses."

28:46.812 --> 28:48.030
Ah.

28:48.161 --> 28:50.816
Okay, gimme, gimme.

28:50.946 --> 28:53.906
A local bar is naming
a wing sauce after me,

28:54.036 --> 28:55.690
but so far,
none of these samples

28:55.821 --> 28:58.345
have been nearly hot enough.

28:58.475 --> 29:01.304
These sauces have
simply been too mild

29:01.435 --> 29:04.699
for the
Worcester Wild...

29:04.830 --> 29:07.397
Dude.

29:07.528 --> 29:10.357
You want to, uh,
write that down?

29:10.487 --> 29:12.968
Nah.

29:13.099 --> 29:16.276
Um, Neil, uh, why don't you
go grab us some, uh,

29:16.406 --> 29:19.409
afternoon tea
and leave the room?

29:19.540 --> 29:21.281
Yep. On it.
Of course.

29:25.807 --> 29:27.374
[Exhales sharply]

29:40.648 --> 29:41.997
What's this?

29:42.128 --> 29:45.087
Uh, I'm gonna
get out of here.

29:45.218 --> 29:46.915
Why?
I have a work thing,

29:47.046 --> 29:49.309
and then, um,
I'm gonna head to my brother's.

29:49.439 --> 29:50.919
He's got a pullout.

29:51.050 --> 29:52.268
His kid won't shut up
about "Frozen,"

29:52.399 --> 29:53.879
but he's got a pullout.

29:54.009 --> 29:56.707
Dude, you don't --

29:56.838 --> 29:58.884
If you want to stay here,
you can stay here.

29:59.014 --> 30:00.146
[Scoffs]

30:04.890 --> 30:06.456
Do you want me to stay?

30:09.198 --> 30:10.286
Yeah.

30:10.852 --> 30:12.593
[Sighs]
U--

30:12.723 --> 30:19.382
♪

30:19.513 --> 30:21.689
[Sighs]

30:21.820 --> 30:25.214
♪

30:25.345 --> 30:27.521
Neil: Hey, give me that.Allison: No, stop.

30:27.651 --> 30:29.175
Give me.
That's not yours.

30:29.305 --> 30:31.177
Aah! No, no!

30:31.307 --> 30:33.048
Aah! Aah!

30:33.179 --> 30:34.136
Give me that. Hey, hey.Stop! Stop!

30:34.267 --> 30:35.485
Give me my phone.

30:35.616 --> 30:38.184
[Screaming]

30:38.314 --> 30:39.185
[Glass shatters]

30:39.315 --> 30:41.361
[Teakettle whistling]

30:41.491 --> 30:50.109
♪

30:50.239 --> 30:52.241
Neil, why does
the kettle sound like

30:52.372 --> 30:55.462
Allison trying to explain
something to me?

30:55.592 --> 30:57.246
Sorry.
I-I drifted.

30:57.377 --> 30:59.858
Neil, what did I say
about drifting?

30:59.988 --> 31:02.773
Both: "It's only for cars
in the Tokyo-based installment

31:02.904 --> 31:04.950
of the 'Fast and the Furious'
franchise."

31:05.080 --> 31:07.866
Right. It was true then,
it's even truer now.

31:07.996 --> 31:10.129
Come on, bud.
I need you to get focused.

31:10.259 --> 31:12.087
I know, I know.
I'm trying.

31:12.218 --> 31:16.091
A-And you've been such
a wonderful, if demanding, boss.

31:16.222 --> 31:18.267
But I need to get
my head on straight.

31:18.398 --> 31:20.008
I gotta
tell you something.

31:20.139 --> 31:21.749
Didn't you just tell me
something, like, last week?

31:21.880 --> 31:24.143
I mean, what else
could there be?

31:24.273 --> 31:26.885
Sh-- She's trying
to kill you.

31:28.451 --> 31:30.018
The reporter?

31:30.149 --> 31:32.934
I mean, that is an awfully
short skirt she's wearing.

31:33.065 --> 31:34.457
No, no, no, no.

31:34.588 --> 31:36.155
Not the reporter.

31:36.285 --> 31:38.200
Allison.

31:38.331 --> 31:40.289
Allison tried
to kill you.

31:40.420 --> 31:42.552
Oh, that?
Oh, yeah, I knew about that.

31:42.683 --> 31:44.119
What?
Yeah.

31:44.250 --> 31:45.816
I mean, Neil,
what is marriage

31:45.947 --> 31:48.558
if not a death sentence,
right?

31:48.689 --> 31:51.344
No, no, no, Kev, she tried --You know, that's actually
a pretty good line.

31:51.474 --> 31:53.346
I'm gonna say that
to the lady reporter

31:53.476 --> 31:55.261
to explain why
the Worcester Wild Dude

31:55.391 --> 31:57.045
has been
a bachelor for life.

31:57.176 --> 31:58.394
Let's go!No, Kev, wait.

31:58.525 --> 31:59.526
She -- She hired --

31:59.656 --> 32:00.919
But grab
those drinks first.

32:03.356 --> 32:05.401
Sorry about that.
Ready when you are.

32:05.532 --> 32:07.882
Okay.
We are all set.

32:08.013 --> 32:11.407
So, Kevin, what would you say
is your best quality?

32:11.538 --> 32:13.932
That's a wonderful question,
Kelly.

32:14.062 --> 32:18.545
I'd say that my best quality
is probably my ability

32:18.675 --> 32:22.027
to keep total cool
in any situation.

32:26.335 --> 32:29.556
Would you care
to elaborate on that?

32:29.686 --> 32:31.427
[Exhales sharply]

32:31.558 --> 32:34.300
Oh, uh,
a-are you okay?

32:34.430 --> 32:36.911
Ah!
A-Are the wings
too spicy?

32:37.042 --> 32:39.740
[Muffled]
No. No. No.

32:39.870 --> 32:41.437
No.

32:41.568 --> 32:43.570
[Grunts]
Uh, no, it's --

32:43.700 --> 32:46.312
[Laughs] Good.
It's just, uh --

32:46.442 --> 32:48.183
Not too spicy.
I love spicy.

32:48.314 --> 32:49.619
[Laughs]
I love spicy.

32:49.750 --> 32:51.708
You know --

32:51.839 --> 32:53.580
Aah!

32:53.710 --> 32:55.495
Whoo!
Is it hot in here?

32:55.625 --> 32:59.020
[Breathing heavily]

32:59.151 --> 33:00.804
Oh, God.

33:00.935 --> 33:02.981
Ooh! Eyes! Ah!

33:03.111 --> 33:06.245
It's, uh --
It's just my eyes are sweaty.

33:06.375 --> 33:07.637
I got sweaty eyes.

33:07.768 --> 33:09.422
Are you sure
you don't need anything?

33:09.552 --> 33:11.250
No, no, no.
A brief --

33:11.380 --> 33:13.992
I'll be -- be right back.
I promise I'll be right back.

33:14.122 --> 33:16.429
[Grunts]
I'm great. Don't worry.

33:16.559 --> 33:17.996
Alright, I got...

33:20.737 --> 33:22.087
...the tea.

33:22.217 --> 33:24.089
[Groaning]

33:28.006 --> 33:30.530
Oh, it feels so good
to get the cold cream

33:30.660 --> 33:32.532
on the old
money-maker, you know?

33:35.013 --> 33:37.972
Now, what was
your question?

33:39.887 --> 33:43.021
♪

33:43.151 --> 33:44.805
Hey, D, it's me.

33:44.935 --> 33:47.025
Uh, I need to get into the
storage unit again tomorrow,

33:47.155 --> 33:49.157
'cause there's got to be
some more of Kevin's stuff

33:49.288 --> 33:50.854
I can hock.

33:50.985 --> 33:52.247
Hock.

33:52.378 --> 33:54.597
Yeah, hock. Ho--
It di-- didn't sound right.

33:54.728 --> 33:56.730
Uh, anyway, call me back.
Bye.

34:00.168 --> 34:01.822
Kelly?

34:01.952 --> 34:04.390
Oh, my God.
Allison Devine?

34:04.520 --> 34:07.001
Hi.
Hi.

34:07.132 --> 34:08.524
What are you
doing here?

34:08.655 --> 34:12.267
I'm interviewing
this ridiculous guy --

34:12.398 --> 34:15.575
Wait, what are you doing here?
Do you live here?

34:15.705 --> 34:18.708
Uh, yeah. That ridiculous guy
is my husband.

34:18.839 --> 34:20.188
Oh.
Sorry.

34:20.319 --> 34:22.234
Ah, it doesn't matter.

34:22.364 --> 34:24.410
He's actually,
you know --

34:24.540 --> 34:26.716
The readers are gonna love him.
I mean, it's Worcester.

34:26.847 --> 34:30.242
Yeah, you bet.
You bet.

34:30.372 --> 34:34.159
So, uh, you work
at the Chronicle.

34:34.289 --> 34:36.074
That's cool.

34:36.204 --> 34:37.684
Yeah.

34:37.814 --> 34:40.774
You wanna come in,
answer some questions with him?

34:40.904 --> 34:43.342
No. No.
He's all yours.

34:43.472 --> 34:45.300
No one wants
to read about me.

34:45.431 --> 34:48.782
You were in the paper like
every other week in high school.

34:48.912 --> 34:51.654
Well, that was
a long time ago.

34:51.785 --> 34:53.569
Come on. I could put
a little thing in there

34:53.700 --> 34:56.790
about that relay junior year
at Nationals.

34:56.920 --> 34:59.227
We could relive our glory days
a little bit.

34:59.358 --> 35:02.361
I don't know if they're glory
days if you come in second.

35:02.491 --> 35:04.885
Well, we would have probably
come in first that next year

35:05.015 --> 35:06.060
if you hadn't have bailed.

35:06.191 --> 35:07.366
[Chuckles]

35:09.933 --> 35:13.154
I just mean --
I didn't get it.

35:13.285 --> 35:15.722
You probably could've gone
to college or something.

35:15.852 --> 35:19.117
Maybe not BC
but, like, a state school.

35:19.247 --> 35:21.075
I never really
thought about it.

35:21.206 --> 35:22.511
What do you mean?

35:22.642 --> 35:25.123
Everybody wanted
to get out of here.

35:25.253 --> 35:28.474
You at least had a shot.

35:28.604 --> 35:30.911
No.

35:31.041 --> 35:32.652
No, I really didn't.

35:32.782 --> 35:40.747
♪

35:40.877 --> 35:48.842
♪

35:48.972 --> 35:56.893
♪

35:57.024 --> 35:59.418
[Coughs]

35:59.548 --> 36:02.421
Oh, thank God.

36:02.551 --> 36:04.423
For a second,
I wasn't sure it was you.

36:04.553 --> 36:08.035
♪

36:08.166 --> 36:09.906
I don't want
to be me anymore.

36:10.037 --> 36:15.173
♪

36:15.303 --> 36:17.523
And I am so sorry,
but I need your help.

36:17.653 --> 36:21.004
♪

36:24.660 --> 36:26.836
[Down-tempo music plays]

36:26.967 --> 36:28.925
[Indistinct conversations]

36:29.056 --> 36:37.934
♪

36:38.065 --> 36:46.900
♪

36:47.030 --> 36:47.901
Hi.

36:48.031 --> 36:49.337
♪

36:49.468 --> 36:52.035
-Officers, hello.
-Hi.

36:52.166 --> 36:53.428
I'll see you later?Okay.

36:53.559 --> 36:56.170
Let us know
if you need anything.Thank you.

36:56.301 --> 36:57.389
Patty: Ugh.

36:57.519 --> 36:59.652
♪

36:59.782 --> 37:01.784
I'm sorry,
is this a funeral?

37:01.915 --> 37:04.744
You said you were
at a work thing.
I am.

37:04.874 --> 37:08.356
Oh, you forgot to mention
the people in mourning part.

37:08.487 --> 37:10.532
Well, it's for Bram,

37:10.663 --> 37:13.579
so there are really like
only two people really mourning.

37:13.709 --> 37:16.886
Both are his sisters, and both
are as horrible as he was.

37:17.017 --> 37:19.759
Uh, he was your partner.

37:19.889 --> 37:21.848
Yes.
He was from Charlestown,

37:21.978 --> 37:24.024
and I was his gay,
black, lady partner.

37:24.154 --> 37:26.200
Oh.Guess how that went?

37:26.331 --> 37:29.247
I cut him slack when he was
alive, but that's done.

37:29.377 --> 37:32.859
Besides,
he died on the john.

37:32.989 --> 37:36.993
It's hard to find that tragic,
even with Elvis.

37:37.124 --> 37:39.344
So, this is why
you've been so sensitive?

37:39.474 --> 37:41.650
I'mbeing sensitive?Yeah.

37:41.781 --> 37:43.478
You left.

37:43.609 --> 37:47.395
Okay, I get that
you're new to this.

37:47.526 --> 37:49.876
Women?
Feelings.

37:50.006 --> 37:51.878
I can deal with the commitment
freakout or whatever,

37:52.008 --> 37:53.749
but I'm not gonna stick around
where I'm not wanted.

37:53.880 --> 37:57.362
You are.
You are. I --

37:57.492 --> 38:00.060
Okay,
I know I can be --

38:00.190 --> 38:01.540
Resentful?

38:01.670 --> 38:04.325
Stubborn?

38:04.456 --> 38:05.544
Cold?

38:05.674 --> 38:08.068
Okay,
maybe don't guess.

38:08.198 --> 38:11.680
I don't love sharing.

38:11.811 --> 38:15.205
I'm bad at it.
So, I guess --

38:15.336 --> 38:17.686
I'm sorry.
I was feeling a little invaded.

38:17.817 --> 38:19.601
I remembered that you
didn't like cashews.

38:19.732 --> 38:23.388
Yeah. I obviously have
a lot of shit to figure out.

38:23.518 --> 38:26.173
Whoo! [Laughs]

38:26.304 --> 38:28.697
Baggage.

38:28.828 --> 38:32.701
I swear to you,
I am working on it.

38:32.832 --> 38:34.921
Because I really do
want you around.

38:35.051 --> 38:37.315
♪

38:37.445 --> 38:38.490
A lot.

38:38.620 --> 38:41.667
♪

38:41.797 --> 38:44.191
Okay?

38:44.322 --> 38:45.192
Okay.

38:45.323 --> 38:51.546
♪

38:51.677 --> 38:54.462
We really can't make out
at a funeral.

38:54.593 --> 38:56.943
You sure?
Yeah.

38:57.073 --> 38:59.989
But, um, you want
to stay for a bit?

39:00.120 --> 39:05.125
I mean, Bram was the worst,
but he gave us an open bar.

39:05.255 --> 39:08.737
I'd love to,
but I can't tonight.

39:08.868 --> 39:10.304
[Sighs]

39:10.435 --> 39:12.262
Why?

39:12.393 --> 39:13.916
Baggage.

39:14.047 --> 39:18.704
But I swear,
I'm working on it.

39:18.834 --> 39:22.272
♪

39:22.403 --> 39:23.622
You look good.

39:23.752 --> 39:27.408
♪

39:27.539 --> 39:29.062
I am so sorry
for your loss.

39:29.192 --> 39:30.803
-Thanks.
-Thank you.

39:30.933 --> 39:36.635
♪

39:36.765 --> 39:39.725
Gentlemen, we are here
to celebrate victory.

39:39.855 --> 39:43.424
Somehow, I was able to rally
and spin Neil's failure --

39:43.555 --> 39:45.992
My failure?Yes, I'm glad you agree.

39:46.122 --> 39:49.691
Your failure into an article
that the newspaper lady

39:49.822 --> 39:54.304
previewed as
"Exactly what she expected."

39:54.435 --> 39:57.873
Oh, and despite Allison blowing
my cover about being married

39:58.004 --> 40:01.747
and Neil's short yet disastrous
tenure as my assistant --

40:01.877 --> 40:03.183
Wait, I'm fired?Yes.

40:03.313 --> 40:06.360
I-I'm glad you agree
that you should be fired.

40:06.491 --> 40:08.754
The Worcester Wild Dude
continues his journey

40:08.884 --> 40:11.278
towards fame
and worldwide influence.

40:11.409 --> 40:14.760
Oh, I feel
dumber already.

40:14.890 --> 40:16.544
Hey, where are you
off to?

40:16.675 --> 40:17.719
Hanging out with Patty.

40:17.850 --> 40:19.242
Oh, she's still next door?

40:19.373 --> 40:21.419
I assumed she'd moved in
with the lady cop by now.

40:21.549 --> 40:23.551
No, no.
That's on the third date.

40:23.682 --> 40:25.335
[Both laugh]

40:25.466 --> 40:27.163
Leave her alone.Leave her alone.

40:27.294 --> 40:29.339
Hey, uh, if you see
Tammy over there,

40:29.470 --> 40:31.211
will you tell her
that the Worcester Wild Dude

40:31.341 --> 40:33.518
wants to do a ride-along.

40:33.648 --> 40:35.911
And I want a key
to the city.Okay.

40:36.042 --> 40:37.913
And a-a milkshake!

40:38.044 --> 40:39.349
I love being famous.

40:39.480 --> 40:41.003
[Both laugh][Bottles clink]

40:41.134 --> 40:45.573
♪

40:45.704 --> 40:46.792
[Dog barking in distance]

40:46.922 --> 40:48.402
This guy
couldn't have met you

40:48.533 --> 40:51.405
in a well-lit coffee shop
or an office or something?

40:51.536 --> 40:55.365
Well, he picked the spot.
I didn't want to put him out.

40:55.496 --> 40:57.629
Are you that surprised
I'm bad at negotiating?

40:57.759 --> 41:00.066
No. Once, I saw you
pay Kevin $20

41:00.196 --> 41:01.850
so he wouldn't wear
sweats to a wake.

41:01.981 --> 41:05.419
Yeah, my cousin's,
and he wore cargo shorts.

41:05.550 --> 41:08.204
Well, I will let you do
the negotiating from now for us.

41:08.335 --> 41:09.989
Allison, no.

41:10.119 --> 41:12.600
I am not here for us,
okay?

41:12.731 --> 41:17.344
I am helping you
with this one last...thing.

41:17.475 --> 41:19.172
Just say it.
Fake my own death.

41:19.302 --> 41:21.827
Because when you go, you're
talking all this shit with you

41:21.957 --> 41:24.220
and everything
you dragged me into.
I know.

41:24.351 --> 41:26.745
Tammy is still asking questions
about Nick.

41:26.875 --> 41:28.964
We broke my brother.

41:29.095 --> 41:30.183
Ever since I actually
made the decision

41:30.313 --> 41:32.011
to start talking to you,

41:32.141 --> 41:35.362
I don't think that I've had
one day that's felt normal.

41:35.493 --> 41:36.755
Or easy.

41:36.885 --> 41:38.234
You're pretty much
a pain in my ass,

41:38.365 --> 41:41.673
and most days...

41:43.762 --> 41:44.806
...you suck.

41:47.592 --> 41:49.289
I know that, too.

41:50.333 --> 41:53.293
♪

41:53.423 --> 41:54.512
Well, if you're gonna be
angry drinking,

41:54.642 --> 41:56.296
the least you could do
is share.

41:56.426 --> 41:58.733
It's vodka.
You hate vodka.

41:58.864 --> 42:00.082
How do you know that?

42:00.213 --> 42:01.649
You said it once.

42:01.780 --> 42:03.825
♪

42:03.956 --> 42:06.001
Patty: Don't run.

42:06.132 --> 42:08.047
-Stop.
-Hi.

42:08.177 --> 42:10.179
Took you long enough.

42:10.310 --> 42:11.441
Sorry.

42:11.572 --> 42:14.053
We had to walk.

42:14.183 --> 42:15.533
To a deserted
parking lot.

42:15.663 --> 42:17.447
Can you do anything alone?
Who's this?

42:17.578 --> 42:19.232
Wh-- Protection.

42:19.362 --> 42:20.668
For the deserted
parking lot.

42:20.799 --> 42:22.496
Well, this felt safest.

42:22.627 --> 42:26.935
I can't go to my office
right now or house.

42:27.066 --> 42:28.720
Are you sure
about this guy?

42:28.850 --> 42:32.419
Chuck heard I met with Diane
and thinks I helped her leave.

42:32.550 --> 42:34.900
Took a bat
to the Wagoneer.

42:35.030 --> 42:35.988
Wait, what?

42:36.118 --> 42:37.642
I love this car.

42:37.772 --> 42:39.731
No, no, no, no.
What do you mean "leave"?

42:39.861 --> 42:42.255
Apparently, she's on the road
to South Carolina.

42:42.385 --> 42:45.519
Took off in the middle of
the night, left Chuck a note.

42:45.650 --> 42:47.216
God help her.

42:49.654 --> 42:52.613
So [Sighs] the $350.

42:52.744 --> 42:55.181
[Sighs]
Yeah, um...

42:57.183 --> 43:00.665
Well, this is, uh --
this worth a lot more than that.

43:03.232 --> 43:05.234
You really are bad
at negotiating.

43:07.062 --> 43:08.716
You two seem like
a lot of work.

43:10.849 --> 43:12.938
But you have my services.

43:13.068 --> 43:15.157
Great.So, what are you after?

43:15.288 --> 43:16.942
Another cheating husband?

43:17.072 --> 43:19.727
Maybe you want to track down
your birth parents?

43:19.858 --> 43:23.209
Uh, no.
This is, uh...

43:23.339 --> 43:26.342
much, much more complicated
than that.

43:26.473 --> 43:27.953
We're a lot of work.

43:32.000 --> 43:32.914
[Laughter]

43:33.045 --> 43:34.046
Hi.
Hi.

43:34.176 --> 43:35.351
[Laughter]

43:35.482 --> 43:36.744
I'm Kevin.Run for your life.

43:36.875 --> 43:38.311
[Audience laughter]

43:38.441 --> 43:40.618
Patti: She's freaked out
and doesn't want to go along.

43:40.748 --> 43:43.446
It's just Allison.
You really can't blow her off.

43:43.577 --> 43:45.405
Wow.
Sorry, I said I would try

43:45.535 --> 43:47.189
with her, and I will.

43:47.320 --> 43:49.801
This is your best bet
for a new identity.

43:49.931 --> 43:51.541
♪

43:51.672 --> 43:55.502
Look for a name and background
that works.

43:55.633 --> 43:57.330
Who the hell
is this guy?

43:57.460 --> 44:01.160
♪

44:02.552 --> 44:12.084
♪

44:12.214 --> 44:21.920
♪

44:22.050 --> 44:31.843
♪
